title: Christians, Inc.
content:
Christians, Inc. is a family owned and operated insurance restoration company established in 1990. Working out of our 18,000 square foot office, warehouse, and showroom in Chanhassen, MN, we have served the needs of over 13,000 businesses and homeowners throughout the Twin Cities metro area.

Visit ChristiansInc.com

WEBSITE UPDATE & REDESIGN

Christians, Inc. has been online since 1999 and hired my services to assist with creating a new look for their website as well as update content to match or outperform their industry competitors online.

Project Requirements:

  • Contact Form
  • Update Photos
  • Update Information about Services

Project Achievements:

  • Competitive analysis of industry competitors' websites
  • Created content based off of analysis to provide better services
  • Added new content other competitors lacked such as modern comparative images, easy drop-down contact forms, and FAQs about services.
  • Added COVID-19 information & business operation facts based on research from other restoration companies, WHO, and industry standards for emergency services.
  • Added new ways interested clients can contact Christians, Inc. with placed advertisements on the sidebar/footer.
  • Arranged content based on how users would easily find information, especially during an emergency.
  • Edited project before/after photos for a brighter appearance and to provide website look & feel uniformity.

MN CHAOS SOFTBALL

A secondary goal was to create a website location for MN Chaos Softball within the ChristiansInc.com website, as the owners of the company have been coaching and sponsoring the local team for over 10 years.

The softball team website required content included having a photo gallery and contact information.

With this new website, returning or interested players, parents, news stations, and local community events can contact Christians, Inc. to learn about MN Chaos Softball, sponsorship opportunities, and community involvement actions.

The website layout within ChristiansInc.com also takes on a different look & feel to help users identify that they are within a new section of the website specifically dedicated to MN Chaos softball.

New and returning players can also pre-register for the season as well as keep up-to-date with events posted on the MN Chaos homepage. These events also sync to their phone calendars and the new website makes it easy to users to stay connected at all times.

title: Bobcat Doosan
content:
Bobcat is a global brand with employees and manufacturing facilities worldwide. We are proud of what we create, the value we provide and the relationships we build – all while helping people succeed. Customers use our machines and technologies to accomplish more in construction, agriculture, landscaping, rental, grounds maintenance, utilities and other applications.  Both the people behind our brand and the equipment we manufacture are tough, agile and versatile. Bobcat equipment fosters a sense of pride and inspires confidence on even the most challenging job sites.

WWW.BOBCAT.COM

Sales & Marketing Co-op

PROJECTS

  • Edited, added and arranged internal website for Bobcat DealerNET and Doosan DealerNET content using a content management site (CMS) called Salesforce and Teamsite.  HTML and CSS were also used while editing.  These languages have been utilized on the job at Doosan Bobcat Company while arranging the internal website and crafting the bi-weekly Dealer Update e-newsletter. 
  • Analyzed data monthly using Oracle and intranet systems, spoke with product influencers and compiled data into Excel reports to be distributed.
  • Organized, assembled and edited weekly email content using Salesforce Exact Target for Bobcat and Doosan.
  • Researched, analyzed and created presentation material for benchmark research projects on competitor companies and industry trends.
  • Provided moving logistic assistance and file merging during the Bobcat Doosan headquarters remodel. I lead the intern team with tasked projects including converting physical files into digital files, relocating equipment to new office locations, and creating internal communication items with the marketing staff detailing building remodel updates.

title: X-Golf Woodbury
content:
When you live in Minnesota, sometimes it's hard to get out on the green and practice your golf swings. X-Golf Woodbury's goal was to create advertisements to showcase the ease of playing golf indoors all-year round at their location while taking part in other stellar amenities offered.

X-Golf Woodbury also wanted to know what their competition was up to online. A social media and website analysis was conducted featuring local competitors. From the results, X-Golf Woodbury gained insight and marketing strategies to strengthen their brand and take action online.

title: The City of Fargo
content:
Far More in Fargo

Wearing many hats, I worked within the City of Fargo (COF) Communications Department as their Public Information Coordinator (PIC) overseeing the creation of many influential projects. Each project required different skills, quick adaptation, communication between over 20+ city departments and knowledge of the current events impacting the City of Fargo.

Working closely with the Manager of Communications, Mayor of Fargo and the City Commissioners, I promoted messages internally and externally while ascertaining the integrity of the new COF brand standards recently issued.

Project Snapshots

Website Building

FargoND.gov

Seeking the finish line at North Dakota State University after a quick three year, class packed journey through their Strategic Communications Bachelors Degree program, I took the City of Fargo Marketing Intern position during my last semester of college. In five short months, I lead and built the way to launching the City of Fargo's new website.

Coordinating with the Website Developers, City of Fargo staff from all 20+ departments, and Communications Manager, I created the website merge timeline and executed the necessary steps to keep all departments on track for the May 31, 2017 launch date.

Creations

Content Management System (CMS) How-To Guide for the City of Fargo (COF) and MATBUS Transportation Websites; training courses for both COF and MATBUS employees assisting with the merge; all website pages that were not hosted by specific departments were created by myself and updated with new information.

I served as main contact for all editing questions, look & feel cohesiveness, troubleshooting and conveying to the in-house Website Developers new ideas, issues, and finding solutions to staff requests.

Visit www.FargoND.gov to see the live site.

City of Fargo Department Photo Shoots

Public Information Coordinator (PIC)

To continue having me as a part of the City's staff after the end of the Communications Internship, the Public Information Coordinator (PIC) position was created and approved by the Fargo City Commission for me to apply for. I succeeded in holding onto my position through the application process and continued to work with the City on their evolving projects.

Department Story Telling:
Photography Style

The City conducted two large photo shoots to update website photos, advertisements, videos, and marketing material. The Fall Photo Shoot focused on inner department services within each physical location. The Winter Photo shoot focused on activities within the community, local businesses, and things to do around Fargo.

First, I created the Request for Proposal (RFP) for photography services, interviewed potential photographers, and helped select the winning bid. Then, I interviewed and hired Talent with the Manager of Communications for the shoots. 20+ City Departments were contacted for photo idea requests, organized into photography sessions, and scheduled with staff to complete the visions.

Over 300 photos/events were coordinated
and executed to update the City's photos!

Hard Copy Photo Albums Created

Camera Research & Product Comparisons

New City Hall Project

New City Hall Details

"The new City Hall is completed and open to serve the residents of Fargo. Construction began on the 150,000 square-foot structure in August 2016, with the completion in September 2018. The structure is designed to house Fargo's municipal operations into the next century. It will be a welcome addition to the downtown skyline, as well as to the greater community's character and appeal. The project's architect is T.L. Stroh Architects, general contractor is Olaf Anderson, mechanical contractor is Robert Gibb & Sons and the electrical contractor is Sun Electric."

City of Fargo's Website

My Assigned Role:
Assistant to City Hall Project Manager

  • Serve as first point of contact and coordinator to move 200+ employees from 12 City departments from the old City Hall building to the new City Hall building.
    1. Research and write a Professional Moving Services contract and RFP bid, conduct site reviews and hold interviews for interested companies. 
    2. Evaluate sealed proposals through a Selection Committee, prepare documents for City Commission review and motion to select moving services for the City Hall project.  Moving company was selected and approved by City Commission July 16, 2018.
    3. Communicate with 12 City departments daily May – September 2018 to physically deliver packing supplies, coordinate large-item moves, troubleshoot moving logistics and assist with correct labeling methods to appropriately move items to the correct locations in the new building.
  • Serve as first point of contact to receive new City Hall deliveries, inspect for quality control, communicate to vendors directly about damaged goods, create damage reports, resolve product logistics issues and assure new items for City Hall are in pristine condition.
  • Assemble large and small furniture pieces, carry, push, lift, adjust and place items into the new City Hall facility in which there are no vendors to complete the task.
    June – November 2018
  • Act as an on-call 24/7 personnel to distribute internal communication to vendors and staff regarding departmental moving implications.
  • Research, evaluate, recommend and purchase items to be used in the new City Hall including but not limited to creating an RFP for Plant Services, air cleansing live plants for City Hall, canvases and acrylic art for all City Hall departments, art description stand-offs and  organizing video wall digital content.
